<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 11:40PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Meriwether, Heard, northeastern Troup and southwestern Coweta
Counties through 1215 AM EDT...
At 1140 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Franklin, moving east
at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Newnan, Franklin, Hogansville, Grantville, Centralhatchee, Moreland,
Lone Oak, East Newnan, Corinth, Powers Crossroads, Handy, Texas and
Harrisonville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
